data.enText: to give sth a smooth even shape so that it can move quickly and easily through air or water

data.chText: 这些汽车都是流线型新款。
data.enText: The cars all have a new streamlined design.

data.chText: 使（系统、机构等）效率更高；（尤指）使增产节约
data.enText: to make a system, an organization, etc. work better, especially in a way that saves money
The production process is to be streamlined.

means: 使(系统、机构等)效率更高

value.def: To streamline an organization or process means to make it more efficient by removing unnecessary parts of it.

example.ex: They're making efforts to streamline their normally cumbersome bureaucracy...
example.tran: 他们正努力精简本来繁冗复杂的官僚体制。

example.ex: They say things should be better now that they have streamlined application procedures.
example.tran: 他们称鉴于他们已经简化了申请手续，情况应该会有所好转。

value.tran: 使(机构或过程)效率更高;精简

example.tran: 雇用廉价自由职业者的精简高效的公司
